# Vitest conventions

## Imports

Always use named imports from `vitest`. Never use `import * as vitest` or globals.

```ts
import { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach, afterEach } from "vitest";
```

For component tests, import from `@testing-library/react`:

```ts
import { render, screen } from "@testing-library/react";
```

## File structure

Group tests with `describe` blocks. Use section separator comments to delineate
groups within a file:

```ts
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Group name
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
```

## Mocking

**Module mocks** â€” declare with `vi.mock()` at the top level, outside any
`describe` or `it`:

```ts
vi.mock("@/lib/data", () => ({
  getPrototypes: mockGetPrototypes,
}));
```

**Hoisted handles** â€” when a mock variable must be referenced inside a
`vi.mock()` factory, declare it with `vi.hoisted()`:

```ts
const { mockFn } = vi.hoisted(() => ({
  mockFn: vi.fn(),
}));
```

**Node built-ins** â€” use `importOriginal` to preserve non-mocked exports and
include an explicit `default` key alongside named exports:

```ts
vi.mock("net", async (importOriginal) => {
  const actual = await importOriginal<typeof import("net")>();
  return { ...actual, default: { ...actual, Socket: MockSocket } };
});
```

**Reset mocks** â€” call `vi.clearAllMocks()` in `beforeEach`, not `afterEach`.

**Fake timers** â€” enable in `beforeEach`, restore in `afterEach`:

```ts
beforeEach(() => { vi.useFakeTimers(); });
afterEach(() => { vi.useRealTimers(); });
```

## API route tests

Import route handlers dynamically inside `beforeEach` (after mocks are set up):

```ts
beforeEach(async () => {
  vi.clearAllMocks();
  ({ POST } = await import("@/app/api/my-route/route"));
});
```

Instantiate `NextRequest` directly; do not use `fetch` or `supertest`:

```ts
new NextRequest("http://localhost/api/path", { method: "POST", headers: { ... } });
```

## Component tests

Prefer semantic queries over implementation queries:

```ts
// Prefer
screen.getByRole("heading", { level: 1 })
screen.getByRole("button", { name: /submit/i })

// Avoid
container.querySelector("h1")
screen.getByTestId("submit-btn")
```

Use `.closest()` when you need the containing element rather than the text node:

```ts
const p = screen.getByText("Hello").closest("p");
```

Do not use snapshot tests.

## Test factory helpers

Extract repeated setup into small named factory functions co-located in the
test file rather than using `beforeEach` for complex object construction:

```ts
function makeRequest(method: "GET" | "POST", port: string) {
  return new NextRequest(`http://localhost/api/prototypes/${port}`, {
    method,
    headers: { authorization: "Bearer test-secret" },
  });
}
```

## Assertions

Use semantic matchers over boolean checks:

```ts
// Prefer
expect(el).toHaveTextContent("Title")
expect(el).toBeInTheDocument()
expect(els).toHaveLength(2)

// Avoid
expect(el.textContent).toBe("Title")
expect(!!el).toBe(true)
expect(els.length).toBe(2)
```

Use `toBeNull()` to assert absence, not `toBeFalsy()`.
